longBusinessSummary: Highland Copper Company Inc., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral projects in the United States. The company explores for copper deposits. It owns the Copperwood copper project; and the White Pine copper project located in the Upper Peninsula of Michigan. The company was formerly known as Highland Resources Inc. and changed its name to Highland Copper Company Inc. in October 2012. Highland Copper Company Inc. is based in Longueuil, Canada.
